text.section:
This section does not apply to:
a parent of the child;
an individual related to the child by blood or marriage within 4 degrees of consanguinity under the civil law rule;
a guardian of the child;
a person who exercises temporary custody or control over the child at the request of a parent or guardian of the child and who is not required otherwise to be licensed;
a person who has the care, custody, or control of the child through placement by a parent or grandparent of the child in contemplation of adoption, if the requirements of § 5-507(b)(2) and (c) of the Family Law Article are met;
an institution that has a child care institution license under this subtitle or § 5-509 of the Family Law Article;
an institution operated by a unit of the State or a political subdivision; or
a foster care provider with whom the child is placed by:
a licensed child placement agency;
a local department of social services;
the Secretary of Health and Mental Hygiene;
the Department; or
a court of competent jurisdiction.
